<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-11-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-11-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="350" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d350">
                        <head>350. Telegram 1097 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d350fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files,
                                611.93/11–855. Confidential.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-11-08">November 8, 1955, 9
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d350-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d350-1"/>
                        <p>1097. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Following from [<hi rend="italic">text not declassified</hi>]
                            correspondent, from source in CHICOM Embassy in East Germany: <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang Ping-nan</persName> under instructions
                            continue Geneva talks as long as necessary; CHICOMS willing continue
                            talks for possibly a year. According to source, at last meeting
                                <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> informed <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName> that Peiping prepared
                            negotiate with Chiang <pb facs="0535" n="488" type="typeset" xml:id="pg_488"/> Kai-shek, willing grant Taiwan “autonomous area”
                            status under Chiang for a period of time.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1"><hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>